** The core capability requirements for this role are: **

• Provide technical leadership, mentoring and advice to a group of ICT
professionals involved in the operational support and maintenance of a diverse
range of enterprise class server, SAN, virtualisation, and Data Centre
infrastructure.  
• Lead the analysis and timely resolution of system issues within a complex
ICT environment.  
• Co-ordinate and manage the identification, assessment and briefing to staff
and management of new and emerging software technologies, products, methods,
techniques, and services.  
• Assist with introduction and use of techniques, methodologies, tools, and
services to match overall current and future business requirements.  
• Engage with vendors, other business units and management to develop
successful working relationships that enhance the effective management of the
Data Centre environment.  
• Manage the implementation of processes and procedures, tools, and techniques
for designing, monitoring, managing, and reporting on the performance and
availability of ICT systems and services.

** Highly Desirable skills/requirements: **

• Operating Systems (Windows Server 2008/2012, RedHat Linux, HPUX)  
• Active Directory, ADFS  
• Email (MS Exchange), Exchange Online  
• Virtual Infrastructure (VMware ESX/ESXi5.x/6.x, vCentre, SRM, View)  
• Backup and Restore (EMC Networker, Data Domain, EMC Avamar, IBM TSM)  
• Monitoring/Alerting (SCOM, Splunk, ObserveIT)  
• Management (HP OneView, IBM Director, Dell OpenManage)  
• Scripting (PowerShell)  
• SAN Technologies (EMC Unisphere VMAX//VNX/Centera/VPLEX, IBM SVC/V7000,
Hitachi HUS)

** Desirable skills/requirements: **

• Directory Services (Group Policy)  
• DNS / DHCP / WINS  
• Windows Clustering / Network Load Balancing  
• Windows Distributed File System  
• Microsoft SQL  
• Microsoft System Centre Configuration Manager (SCCM)  
• Microsoft System Centre Operations Manager (SCOM)  
• Cloud hosting operations support (Azure, AWS)

** Special Conditions **

This position is required to:

• Perform some duties after-hours on a scheduled basis.  
• Provide on-call support as part of a 24/7 roster.  
• Undertake occasional shift work as required.

